**Overall Meaning:**

This verse encourages the seeker to dissolve the ego and identify with the pure, conscious Self. It advises placing the ego, which is attached to the body, within the eternal bliss of the conscious Self and then abandoning the body.  By doing so, the seeker becomes free from the limitations of the physical form and experiences the pure, undifferentiated reality of the Self.

**Translation:**

**In the conscious Self, in eternal bliss, place the ego clinging to the body, and then abandon the body.  Become pure, always.** 
